adjectives.description: quincuncial (comparative more quincuncial, superlative most quincuncial)

examples: Of this Quincunciall Ordination the Ancients practised much, discoursed little [...].

entries.meaning: (botany) Having the leaves of a pentamerous calyx or corolla so imbricated that two are exterior, two are interior, and the other has one edge exterior and one interior.
